data.name: Cajun Shrimp Tacos
data.quickTastyDescription: Spicy Cajun shrimp wrapped in soft tortillas with crunchy slaw and zesty lime crema.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, toss shrimp with Cajun seasoning and olive oil until well-coated.
Heat a skillet over medium-high heat and add seasoned shrimp. Cook for 2-3 minutes on each side until pink and cooked through.
Meanwhile, in a separate bowl, mix sour cream with lime juice and a pinch of salt to create the crema.
Warm corn tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave until pliable.
Assemble tacos by placing shrimp on tortillas, adding shredded cabbage, avocado slices, and a drizzle of lime crema on top. Garnish with chopped cilantro.
data.detailedName: Cajun Shrimp Tacos with Lime Crema and Avocado
data.modifiersForBase: Cajun spiced shrimp, fresh toppings, and zesty sauce.
